      },
      "date": "2025-02-09 01:08:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nEllis had recently contacted some of the sites that host online Linux man pages (see LUDOC-546), and one of the requests was to split the pages into subdirectories by section (ie. man1/, man3/, man5/, man7/, man8/) so if we are moving all of the pages it makes sense to do that at the same time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e9181c6c478a0af2976ba1c955947392d5b05658",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2025-02-09 17:13:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Ellis had recently contacted some of the sites that host online Linux man pages (see LUDOC-546), and one of the requests was to split the pages into subdirectories by section (ie. man1/, man3/, man5/, man7/, man8/) so if we are moving all of the pages it makes sense to do that at the same time.\n\nThat sounds reasonable. There would probably be a lot less merge conflicts (assuming I split the patch).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5699f3a09a2f602a0e5d6c067470f0e361085127",
      "author": {
