        "email": "elliswilson@microsoft.com",
        "username": "elliswilson"
      },
      "date": "2025-02-10 14:54:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > Ellis had recently contacted some of the sites that host online Linux man pages (see LUDOC-546), and one of the requests was to split the pages into subdirectories by section (ie. man1/, man3/, man5/, man7/, man8/) so if we are moving all of the pages it makes sense to do that at the same time.\n> \n> That sounds reasonable. There would probably be a lot less merge conflicts (assuming I split the patch).\n\nHere's the full context if it is helpful Tim:\nhttps://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-546",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
